node.text:
Trying something a bit different to show the process of how I make my videos! I've done vlogs in the past, but I've typically been too precious with them - setting up tons of cameras, microphones, and reading scripts. Who has the time for that?

So I gave myself the restriction that I could make this video with ONLY my cell phone. That way it wouldn't feel like it was getting in the way and I could keep the energy flowing while filming the actual trick.

Let me know what you think! I kept this under 5 minutes and actually really like it compared to the more proper vlog-style videos I've made.

node.text: Checked out @Sony’s amazing technology at CES for the launch of #BoundlessBySony! This virtual set is unbelievable. The entire environment is projected on screens that react and change to the camera's position in real-time. This offers unlimited creative potential to creators and visual effects artists like myself. If you want to see more, check out Sony's official campaign site at www.sony.com/boundless or link in my bio! #ad
